      <h2>I’m an administrative</h2><p> worker bee (a good one, but still). You can find me by the coffee maker sharing my knowledge of the best restaurants in town, how to pick a great glass of wine, and oddly enough, any bit of celebrity gossip (put <em>THAT</em> in your back pocket for the next office trivia night). However, when I discovered web development, I found my calling, my next career. Most people are like, umm, random... but nothing has ever made more sense to me.</p>
    </div> 
    <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-4">
      <h2>So with a lot of studying,</h2><p> practicing, and massive amounts of coffee, I feel confident enough to call myself a web developer. To start off this new career, my husband and I have decided to take the pups and move to Charlotte, NC.  Here, I'm excited to bring my unique skew on life, enthusiasm for my work, and never-ending quest for knowledge to my new position in web development.</p>
