        <div class="container" style="width:750px">
          <div class="panel-group" id="accordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
              <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingOne">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true"
                  aria-controls="collapseOne"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></span>
                  Where Are You From?
                </a>
              </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingOne">
              <div class="panel-body">
                Good question and one I get asked a lot because of my accent. I grew up mostly in North Carolina, but
                moved around a lot as a kid. My dad is originally from Wisconsin, so I occassionally have these weird
                Mid-Western moments in the midst of my Southern-ness.
                I've lived in Maryland for the past eight years and moved there to be with my boyfriend, now husband. We're
                currently relocating back to the South because quite frankly, I'm tired of digging my car out
                of the snow every Winter. I also miss sweet tea. I'm also very excited to be back closer to family.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingTwo">
              <h4 class="panel-title">
                <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo"
                aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></span>
                What is Your Professional Background?
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingTwo">
            <div class="panel-body">
              Way back in my youth, I decided that a Psychology major was a good idea. Well, it wasn't a bad idea
              because I got a bachelor's degree, but it didn't exactly open a lot of professional doors.
              I worked my way through some administrative jobs after college until my move to Maryland. Once here, I
              landed a job in the much sought-after Government contracting industry. I started in Procurement, moved
              over to Proposal Pricing, and finally into Contracts and Operational Finance. I currently hold an active
              TS/SCI clearance with a full-scope polygraph, should that ever be necessary.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingThree">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree"
              aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></span>
              How Did You End Up in Web Development?
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingThree">
          <div class="panel-body">
            In all my work with Government contracting, I was surrounded by the brightest minds in IT. Yet, I never
            considered myself to be the type that could do that kind of work. I had been on the administrative side of
            things my entire career and expected to be there forever.
            As a hobby, I picked up photography and quickly learned Photoshop and other editing programs. It was
            suggested to me that I might be good at design - and from there my journey began.
            I took design classes, typography classes, advanced Photoshop classes. It wasn't until I stumbled on an
            HTML class that I found my true passion.
            While I like design, I found that I love building. The life-long student in me has continued to learn all
            things web development-related in order to become a well-rounded and knowledgable member of a great
            development team.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel panel-default">
