          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour"
            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></span>
            What is Your Design Process?
          </a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingFour">
        <div class="panel-body">
          First and foremost, I need to understand what needs to be presented. I like to whittle the information
          down to it's smallest parts so I can envision it in little blocks. From there I can expand the blocks as
          needed, or even remove blocks if they don't belong. Once the information piece is complete, then the
          design can take place. I like to start with the most important element and work my way down (or around, or
          sideways, who knows...). I love photography and if the design warrants it, I like to incorporate it
          somehow. I prefer clean designs, but of
          course, the client always comes first and their wish is my command.
        </div>
